STAT3040 : Time Series Analysis 2016 Computer Lab. 9 - Week 10

1. ARMA Models in R

  1. Generate a time series from the MA(3) model \[ X_t=\mathcal{W}_t + 0.8\mathcal{W}_{t-1} + 0.1\mathcal{W}_{t-2} - 0.7\mathcal{W}_{t-3} \]
MA3 <- arima.sim(list(order=c(0,0,3), ma=c(0.8,0.1,-0.7)), n=1000)
acf(MA3)

pacf(MA3)

  1. Generate a time series from the AR(2) model \[ X_t=X_{t-1} - 0.16 X_{t-2} + \mathcal{W}_{t} \]
AR2 <- arima.sim(list(order=c(2,0,0), ar=c(1,-0.16)), n=1000)
acf(AR2, 50)

pacf(AR2, 50)

  1. Calculate the theoretical ACF and PACF of the AR(2) model \[ X_t=X_{t-1} - 0.16 X_{t-2} + \mathcal{W}_{t} \]
ACF4AR2 <- ARMAacf(ar=c(1,-0.16), ma=0, 50)
plot(ACF4AR2, type="h")
abline(h=0)

PACF4AR2 <- ARMAacf(ar=c(1,-0.16), ma=0, 50, pacf=TRUE)
plot(PACF4AR2, type="h")
abline(h=0)

  1. Find the roots of the AR polynomial for the AR(2) model \[ X_t=X_{t-1} - 0.16 X_{t-2} + \mathcal{W}_{t} \]
z <- c(1,-1,0.16)
Roots <- Re(polyroot(z))
Roots
[1] 1.250000000000004 4.999999999999996
  1. Find the theoretical autocorrelation function of the AR(2) model \[ X_t=X_{t-1} - 0.16 X_{t-2} + \mathcal{W}_{t} \] explicitly.
A <- matrix(nrow = 2, ncol = 2)
A[,1] <- c(1,Roots[1])
A[,2] <- c(1,Roots[2])
B <- c(1, 1/1.16)
Sol <- solve(A,B)
Sol
[1]  1.1034482758620703 -0.1034482758620703
  1. Based on the results of Item 5, calculate the ACF in lags 1 and 12 and compare them with ACF4AR2:
# lag 1
Sol[1]*Roots[1]^(-1)+Sol[2]*Roots[2]^(-1)
[1] 0.8620689655172391
# lag -1
Sol[1]*1.25^(1)+Sol[2]*5^(1)
